Goal: We want our user to be able to authenticate
Endgame: have a token in our app (probably in the store)

- Get the credentials from the user (login form) X
- POST to authentication route (THUNK), returns our token X
* use the me endpoint to get some information about the user
- Store it in the store X
- Get the user information using '/me'
- Make authenticated request by putting the token in the header

Goal: Save the token in the browser and use it to authenticate the user on a refresh
- In your login action save the token to the localstorage X
- Get the token out of localstorage (on first render)  X
- Do a request with the token to /me X